#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L04_OddDegVerts
msgid "_credits: github.com/leanprover-community/NNG4_\n"
"# Summary\n"
"\n"
"The §0 tactic can be used to add new hypotheses to a level, but of course\n"
"you have to prove them.  Use §1 for hypothesis/propositions and §2 for explicit objects/functions.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"## Example\n"
"\n"
"The simplest usage is like this. If you have §3 in your context and you execute\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"then you will get a new goal §5 to prove, and after you've proved\n"
"it you will have a new hypothesis §6 in your original goal.\n"
"\n"
"## Example\n"
"\n"
"If you already have a proof of what you want to §7, you\n"
"can just create it immediately. For example, if you have §8 and §9\n"
"number objects, then\n"
"\n"
"§10\n"
"\n"
"will directly add a new hypothesis §11\n"
"to the context, because you just supplied the proof of it (§12).\n"
"\n"
"## Example\n"
"\n"
"If you have a proof to hand, then you don't even need to state what you\n"
"are proving. For example\n"
"\n"
"§13\n"
"\n"
"will add §14 as a hypothesis."
msgstr ""

